cs.DC, cs.SC, cs.NA, cs.CE, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of graphics processing units (GPU) to speed up calculations in gravitational direct N-body simulations. 
- cs.SC (Scientific Computing and Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper involves numerical simulations and the use of integrators to solve equations of motion. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category as the paper discusses the accuracy of the numerical methods used in the simulations. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper involves computational simulations in the field of astrophysics. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on the visualization of the simulations, but rather on the computational methods used to perform them.
